00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:27,285
but we have to be aggressive
to control these seizures.

254
00:11:53,529 --> 00:11:55,508
This is Julian Booth.

255
00:11:55,532 --> 00:11:57,727
Hello, I'm calling from
Medicine Tracking Dynamics.

256
00:11:57,751 --> 00:12:00,835
QuoVadis pays us to
monitor prescription drugs

257
00:12:00,871 --> 00:12:02,920
and alert them of
prospective patients.

258
00:12:02,955 --> 00:12:05,223
<i>There's one at
Chastain Park Memorial</i>

259
00:12:05,258 --> 00:12:07,942
<i>that's now receiving
three anti-seizure meds:</i>

260
00:12:07,977 --> 00:12:10,878
fosphenytoin, valproic
acid and phenobarbital.

261
00:12:10,913 --> 00:12:13,247
Which makes him a VNS candidate.

262
00:12:13,300 --> 00:12:16,133
<i>QuoVadis flagged this as
high priority on your account.</i>

263
00:12:16,168 --> 00:12:18,469
<i>I don't have a patient name,</i>

264
00:12:18,504 --> 00:12:21,906
but the order came
from Chastain ER.

265
00:12:27,930 --> 00:12:29,897
Hey.

266
00:12:29,932 --> 00:12:32,100
You look busy.

267
00:12:32,135 --> 00:12:34,819
Always.

268
00:12:37,857 --> 00:12:40,391
Devon, this doesn't
have to be weird.

269
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:43,311
We are completely
capable of still being friends.

270
00:12:46,365 --> 00:12:48,049
Agreed.

271
00:12:48,084 --> 00:12:50,062
So, friend,

272
00:12:50,086 --> 00:12:51,585
what can I do for you?

273
00:12:51,621 --> 00:12:53,604
I got a call about a patient

274
00:12:53,640 --> 00:12:56,624
in the ER who was just put
on several anti-seizure meds.

275
00:12:56,660 --> 00:12:58,909
Henry Barnett.
Status epilepticus.

276
00:12:58,945 --> 00:13:00,845
He's looking rough.

277
00:13:00,881 --> 00:13:02,913
Poor kid.

278
00:13:02,949 --> 00:13:05,683
His brother died
here a month ago.

279
00:13:05,718 --> 00:13:07,802
I didn't know it was a child.

280
00:13:07,837 --> 00:13:09,487
What's this about?

281
00:13:09,522 --> 00:13:12,840
Um... nothing.

282
00:13:20,550 --> 00:13:22,427
Are you telling
me he has cancer?

283
00:13:22,451 --> 00:13:24,313
- No, that's not...
- Five hours in the ER

284
00:13:24,337 --> 00:13:25,936
only to get in here

285
00:13:25,972 --> 00:13:28,289
to have you look at
us like he's going to die.

286
00:13:28,324 --> 00:13:29,852
- Ms. Waverly,
I know that you're concer...
- Are you a nurse?

287
00:13:29,876 --> 00:13:30,992
What are you?

288
00:13:31,027 --> 00:13:34,178
A med student? This
man is my whole life,

289
00:13:34,214 --> 00:13:36,142
and you're the one
that's going to save him?

290
00:13:36,166 --> 00:13:39,033
No. I want somebody
that doesn't have that look

291
00:13:39,069 --> 00:13:40,935
on their face.

292
00:13:40,970 --> 00:13:43,171
I'm ordering a CT...

293
00:13:45,975 --> 00:13:48,309
a CT to see what is going on

294
00:13:48,345 --> 00:13:49,688
so I can hopefully
rule out cancer.

295
00:13:49,712 --> 00:13:52,313
See you in five hours.

296
00:13:52,349 --> 00:13:55,900
It's okay, baby. Don't worry.

297
00:13:55,935 --> 00:13:57,518
It's okay.

298
00:13:57,553 --> 00:14:00,371
I am enjoying our stroll,

299
00:14:00,406 --> 00:14:02,218
but don't you two
have other things to do?

300
00:14:02,242 --> 00:14:04,536
Are you kidding? I always
have time for my favorite patient.

301
00:14:04,560 --> 00:14:07,228
- We know what today is.
- And we have

302
00:14:07,263 --> 00:14:09,642
no intention of letting
you face it alone, Wallace.

303
00:14:09,666 --> 00:14:12,367
My wife, Anna,
would've been 36 today.

304
00:14:12,402 --> 00:14:14,185
Remember her last birthday

305
00:14:14,220 --> 00:14:17,171
- in ICU? We
threw quite a party.

306
00:14:17,206 --> 00:14:19,590
It's hard to believe

307
00:14:19,626 --> 00:14:22,760
my wife spent the last
year of her life at Chastain.

308
00:14:22,795 --> 00:14:24,390
I don't think there's
a doctor or nurse

309
00:14:24,414 --> 00:14:25,496
who didn't know her.

310
00:14:25,532 --> 00:14:27,198
A great lady.

311
00:14:27,233 --> 00:14:29,434
Think, uh, both of you...

312
00:14:29,469 --> 00:14:31,102
And the whole staff...

313
00:14:31,137 --> 00:14:33,620
Did all you could to save her.

314
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:38,042
Now I'm the patient.

315
00:14:38,078 --> 00:14:40,778
Another year has gone by,

316
00:14:40,813 --> 00:14:42,775
and now it's my turn
to spend my days here,

317
00:14:42,799 --> 00:14:45,266
waiting for a new heart.

318
00:14:45,301 --> 00:14:49,003
And until we find one,
you're stuck with us, Wallace.

319
00:14:49,038 --> 00:14:51,756
Oh, she means
you're stuck with<i> her.</i>

320
00:14:51,791 --> 00:14:54,875
I'm delightful.

321
00:14:54,911 --> 00:14:57,778
Hey.

322
00:14:57,813 --> 00:15:00,081
I heard about Henry.

323
00:15:00,116 --> 00:15:01,865
How's he doing?

324
00:15:01,901 --> 00:15:03,312
Finally broke his seizures.

325
00:15:03,336 --> 00:15:05,114
Now he's reacting
negatively to the medications.

326
00:15:05,138 --> 00:15:07,839
Well, I'm sure Dr. Eckart
has it under control.

327
00:15:08,891 --> 00:15:12,776
He's Henry's doctor now.

328
00:15:18,818 --> 00:15:21,769
I can't step back.

329
00:15:21,804 --> 00:15:24,772
Not after everything I've
seen this family go through.

330
00:15:24,807 --> 00:15:26,824
I know.

331
00:15:26,860 --> 00:15:28,876
But this is why we try

332
00:15:28,911 --> 00:15:31,245
to keep a safe distance
from our patients.

333
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:40,087
- I should get in there.
- Yeah.

334
00:15:43,142 --> 00:15:45,509
Hey, buddy.

335
00:15:45,545 --> 00:15:48,095
- You hanging in there?
- Yeah.

336
00:15:48,131 --> 00:15:50,398
Is this gonna hurt?

337
00:15:50,433 --> 00:15:53,767
Nah. You'll feel a little pinch.

338
00:15:53,803 --> 00:15:55,531
That's just the
numbing medication.

339
00:15:55,555 --> 00:15:57,715
After that all you'll feel
is a little bit of pressure.

340
00:16:02,461 --> 00:16:04,044
You're really brave, baby.

341
00:16:05,565 --> 00:16:07,799
Got a question for you.

342
00:16:07,834 --> 00:16:09,111
Who's your favorite
baseball player?

343
00:16:09,135 --> 00:16:10,968
Bryce Harper.

344
00:16:11,004 --> 00:16:12,714
Washington Nationals.

345
00:16:12,738 --> 00:16:14,421
That is a solid choice.

346
00:16:14,457 --> 00:16:16,757
Tell Dr. Hawkins why
you like Bryce Harper.

347
00:16:16,792 --> 00:16:19,810
His cleats are awesome.

348
00:16:21,730 --> 00:16:23,475
Your decision's
based on footwear?

349
00:16:23,499 --> 00:16:24,932
He's supercool.

350
00:16:24,968 --> 00:16:29,219
Henry, you are one tough kid.

351
00:16:29,255 --> 00:16:30,982
And I bet your
buddy Bryce Harper

352
00:16:31,006 --> 00:16:33,658
would think you're
supercool, too.

353
00:16:37,346 --> 00:16:39,647
<i>This boy</i>

354
00:16:39,682 --> 00:16:41,799
is perfect for the VNS.

355
00:16:41,835 --> 00:16:43,746
I mean, we're never gonna
get a more sympathetic patient.

356
00:16:43,770 --> 00:16:46,003
Spectacular optics.

357
00:16:46,038 --> 00:16:49,339
So, the VNS is approved
for use in pediatric patients?

358
00:16:49,375 --> 00:16:50,869
I'm sure Gordon
has crossed his T's

359
00:16:50,893 --> 00:16:52,660
and dotted the I's on this one.

360
00:16:52,695 --> 00:16:54,023
Indeed, I have. We're approved.

361
00:16:54,047 --> 00:16:56,864
But as a 510 device?

362
00:16:56,899 --> 00:17:00,367
I know. She's worried
because with 510 FDA approval,

363
00:17:00,402 --> 00:17:01,702
there's often no testing

364
00:17:01,737 --> 00:17:04,639
before a device gets
implanted in patients,

365
00:17:04,674 --> 00:17:06,955
which is exactly why
QuoVadis does its own research.

366
00:17:08,561 --> 00:17:10,228
Now, we haven't published yet.

367
00:17:13,950 --> 00:17:16,817
But everything is here,
and it's all that any doctor

368
00:17:16,852 --> 00:17:18,536
could possibly ask for.

369
00:17:18,571 --> 00:17:20,499
If you meet with any
resistance, just don't hesitate

370
00:17:20,523 --> 00:17:23,043
to let me know. I want to make
sure we're all on the same page.

371
00:17:35,204 --> 00:17:37,338
So, are you done?

372
00:17:37,373 --> 00:17:40,390
Should we be concerned
about Micah's heart rate?

373
00:17:40,426 --> 00:17:42,576
Your boy's gonna be fine.

374
00:17:42,611 --> 00:17:43,728
We just need to adjust

375
00:17:43,763 --> 00:17:45,574
his beta-blockers and
order a sleep study.

376
00:17:45,598 --> 00:17:47,448
You can go ahead and button up.

377
00:17:47,483 --> 00:17:50,668
Mina, can I talk to you outside
about a separate matter?

378
00:17:59,561 --> 00:18:01,795
Listen, don't let your
all-consuming worry

379
00:18:01,831 --> 00:18:04,198
for lover boy make
you lose your focus.

380
00:18:04,233 --> 00:18:05,928
Nothing gets in
the way of my work,

381
00:18:05,952 --> 00:18:07,952
and stop calling him lover boy.

382
00:18:07,987 --> 00:18:10,487
It's becoming annoying.

383
00:18:10,523 --> 00:18:13,574
We got a heart.

384
00:18:13,610 --> 00:18:14,837
Dr. Austin, you're
on Wallace Troke's

385
00:18:14,861 --> 00:18:16,288
transplant team
this week, right?

386
00:18:16,312 --> 00:18:18,228
- Just say yes.
- Yes.

387
00:18:18,264 --> 00:18:20,764
Isn't this the dude with
takotsubo cardiomyopathy?

388
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:22,761
- Broken heart syndrome.
- The first case I've seen

389
00:18:22,785 --> 00:18:24,814
where grief literally
broke someone's heart.

390
00:18:24,838 --> 00:18:25,819
His wife, Anna,

391
00:18:25,854 --> 00:18:28,472
died here after a long illness.

392
00:18:28,508 --> 00:18:31,275
Every day for a year he walked
three miles just to be with her

393
00:18:31,311 --> 00:18:32,977
and then three miles back home.

394
00:18:33,012 --> 00:18:34,428
Were there no buses running?

395
00:18:34,464 --> 00:18:35,930
He liked to walk.

396
00:18:35,965 --> 00:18:37,159
Said it made him
feel the importance

397
00:18:37,183 --> 00:18:38,415
of his daily commitment

398
00:18:38,451 --> 00:18:41,102
- to be with her.
- Oh, adorable, if nutty.

399
00:18:41,137 --> 00:18:43,804
His only chance of
surviving is this transplant.

400
00:18:43,839 --> 00:18:45,867
The good news is we found
an organ that's a match.

401
00:18:45,891 --> 00:18:48,259
But we need you to harvest
it at Methodist Memorial.

402
00:18:48,294 --> 00:18:50,677
Have you ever
assisted in the harvest

403
00:18:50,712 --> 00:18:52,091
- of a heart?
- No.

404
00:18:52,115 --> 00:18:54,097
Is that an invitation

405
00:18:54,133 --> 00:18:55,510
- to accompany you?
- Do you need it

406
00:18:55,534 --> 00:18:58,202
- embossed on stationery?
- I do not.

407
00:18:58,237 --> 00:19:00,157
Then let's get
this ball rolling.

408
00:19:08,747 --> 00:19:10,342
Dividing the pulmonary veins

409
00:19:10,366 --> 00:19:12,032
and main P.A.

410
00:19:12,068 --> 00:19:14,518
It is a perfect
organ for Wallace.

411
00:19:20,226 --> 00:19:22,204
And what are we
looking for, Dr. Okafor?

412
00:19:22,228 --> 00:19:26,230
Defects and
vegetations on the valves.

413
00:19:26,265 --> 00:19:27,959
And an adequate
rim of atrial tissue

414
00:19:27,983 --> 00:19:29,650
next to the coronary sinus.

415
00:19:29,702 --> 00:19:32,353
I was getting to that.

416
00:19:32,388 --> 00:19:34,504
I know.

417
00:19:50,873 --> 00:19:52,353
Charge.

418
00:19:56,845 --> 00:19:59,513
Clear.

419
00:20:03,303 --> 00:20:05,886
Ah.

420
00:20:05,939 --> 00:20:08,222
Now, back to Chastain,

421
00:20:08,257 --> 00:20:10,577
where the transplant team
will put this beautiful organ

422
00:20:10,610 --> 00:20:12,375
in our man Wallace.

423
00:20:14,364 --> 00:20:16,842
Henry's LP ruled
out an infection,

424
00:20:16,866 --> 00:20:18,677
and his MRI didn't show
anything concerning.

425
00:20:18,701 --> 00:20:19,784
And that's good news.

426
00:20:19,819 --> 00:20:21,435
Yes, but it still means

427
00:20:21,470 --> 00:20:22,932
we don't know what's
causing his seizures.

428
00:20:22,956 --> 00:20:25,456
Truth is, sometimes
we never know.

429
00:20:25,491 --> 00:20:28,926
Henry's EEG still shows
runs of nonconvulsive seizures.

430
00:20:28,961 --> 00:20:32,045
With their length and frequency,
if this goes on much longer,

431
00:20:32,081 --> 00:20:34,231
he can sustain
permanent brain damage.

432
00:20:34,267 --> 00:20:36,450
Brain damage?

433
00:20:43,409 --> 00:20:45,642
What do you suggest we do now?

434
00:20:45,677 --> 00:20:47,094
If the seizures continue,

435
00:20:47,129 --> 00:20:48,791
we're gonna have to
put Henry into a coma

436
00:20:48,815 --> 00:20:50,281
so that his brain can rest.

437
00:20:50,316 --> 00:20:51,782
Are there any other options?

438
00:20:51,817 --> 00:20:53,818
Actually, there is.

439
00:20:55,855 --> 00:20:58,272
Julian, this is Henry's
mom, Zoey Barnett.

440
00:20:58,307 --> 00:21:01,975
Julian Booth works
with a cutting-edge

441
00:21:02,011 --> 00:21:03,721
new medical device
company, QuoVadis.

442
00:21:03,745 --> 00:21:07,164
I am so sorry Henry's
going though this.

443
00:21:07,200 --> 00:21:09,233
But we may have a solution.

444
00:21:09,268 --> 00:21:11,601
We have a new VNS
device designed for cases

445
00:21:11,637 --> 00:21:13,003
exactly like your son's.

446
00:21:13,039 --> 00:21:15,439
VNS devices are a last resort.

447
00:21:15,475 --> 00:21:17,057
And they've all had

448
00:21:17,093 --> 00:21:19,659
significant side effects,
including sudden death.

449
00:21:19,695 --> 00:21:23,564
This newest version is
thoroughly tested and safe.

450
00:21:23,599 --> 00:21:25,849
This is for Dr. Eckart.

451
00:21:25,884 --> 00:21:27,985
He is the doctor
who makes this call,

452
00:21:28,021 --> 00:21:29,169
along with Henry's mom.

453
00:21:29,204 --> 00:21:31,255
There are trials that show

454
00:21:31,290 --> 00:21:33,185
it can be used much
earlier in epilepsy,

455
00:21:33,209 --> 00:21:36,176
sometimes removing the
need of medications altogether.

456
00:21:36,211 --> 00:21:38,612
If you have access
to an improved VNS

457
00:21:38,647 --> 00:21:40,108
that can be used
sooner in epilepsy,

458
00:21:40,132 --> 00:21:41,681
it's a game-changer.

459
00:21:41,717 --> 00:21:44,968
Henry could lead a
life free of seizures.

460
00:21:45,004 --> 00:21:48,039
If the alternative is
putting Henry in a coma

461
00:21:48,074 --> 00:21:50,936
or keeping him on toxic
meds, isn't this worth the risk?

462
00:21:50,960 --> 00:21:52,326
We don't know that yet.

463
00:21:52,361 --> 00:21:56,108
This is not a decision
I would rush into.

464
00:21:56,132 --> 00:21:58,315
If it were me,

465
00:21:58,350 --> 00:22:00,295
I would have Dr. Eckart
go over all the data,

466
00:22:00,319 --> 00:22:01,599
and then you take it from there.

467
00:22:02,888 --> 00:22:05,689
- Dr. Eckart, would you mind?
- Not at all.

468
00:22:05,724 --> 00:22:07,474
I'll get back to you.

469
00:22:07,509 --> 00:22:09,843
Right.

470
00:22:12,515 --> 00:22:15,616
They'll take you up to
pre-op and get you ready

471
00:22:15,651 --> 00:22:18,202
for when your new
heart gets here.

472
00:22:19,905 --> 00:22:21,722
Thank you.

473
00:22:29,998 --> 00:22:32,833
You worried about the surgery?

474
00:22:34,087 --> 00:22:36,420
If I die...

475
00:22:36,455 --> 00:22:38,472
when I'm under...

476
00:22:38,508 --> 00:22:40,708
I'm ready.

477
00:22:40,743 --> 00:22:42,576
I'll get to be with Anna.

478
00:22:42,611 --> 00:22:45,362
Wallace, this is a
chance at a whole new life.

479
00:22:45,398 --> 00:22:47,347
I'm starting to think

480
00:22:47,383 --> 00:22:50,400
that heart might be better
served in somebody else.

481
00:22:50,436 --> 00:22:54,421
Not sure I want
a whole new life.

482
00:22:54,456 --> 00:22:57,090
Not if it still feels
like this one.

483
00:22:58,144 --> 00:23:00,611
Grief is horrible.

484
00:23:00,646 --> 00:23:03,347
Breaks you into a
million pieces, I know.

485
00:23:03,382 --> 00:23:06,583
But I promise you,

486
00:23:06,619 --> 00:23:09,269
it will get easier.

487
00:23:09,304 --> 00:23:12,423
How?

488
00:23:12,458 --> 00:23:16,059
By keeping Anna's memory alive.

489
00:23:16,095 --> 00:23:18,345
If you die, all that
goes with you.

490
00:23:18,380 --> 00:23:21,915
Who's gonna be here to talk
about how special Anna was?

491
00:23:21,950 --> 00:23:25,785
How amazing you were together?

492
00:23:27,773 --> 00:23:30,457
I'll see you in recovery.

493
00:23:30,493 --> 00:23:32,609
Yeah.

494
00:23:32,644 --> 00:23:35,128
And... and thank you.

495
00:23:38,517 --> 00:23:40,483
Thank you for coming
down to consult.

496
00:23:40,519 --> 00:23:42,302
No problem.

497
00:23:42,337 --> 00:23:45,422
Did you lose a little weight
since the last time I saw you?

498
00:23:45,458 --> 00:23:47,824
The day hasn't
started off so great.

499
00:23:47,859 --> 00:23:49,609
Hi.

500
00:23:49,662 --> 00:23:51,478
Finally, a specialist.

501
00:23:51,514 --> 00:23:53,213
We've been waiting two hours,

502
00:23:53,248 --> 00:23:56,666
and this Indian doctor is
the only one who's seen us.

503
00:23:56,702 --> 00:23:58,463
- What's the story?
- 75-year-old male

504
00:23:58,487 --> 00:24:02,005
with two days abdominal
cramping and vomiting.

505
00:24:02,040 --> 00:24:03,791
CT shows a partial SBO.

506
00:24:03,826 --> 00:24:06,176
Mm-hmm. Okay. Can
I talk to you for a sec?

507
00:24:10,766 --> 00:24:12,732
What is this?

508
00:24:12,768 --> 00:24:14,596
- He has a bowel obstruction.
- Partial.

509
00:24:14,620 --> 00:24:16,248
- With a soft abdomen.
- But he has significant

510
00:24:16,272 --> 00:24:18,255
pain and is still vomiting.

511
00:24:18,290 --> 00:24:19,623
